They are not going to remove AH from Aquaman 2 and they probably won't remove her from Aquaman 3. Her spot is secure and people need to accept that fact. She has not lost any work because of what has happened nor will she, in fact she has more work now than she can handle. Honestly, if you're so childish that you won't see a movie just because one person you dislike is in it, well then go ahead and be that child, that's your call. Just remember that you're not just hurting AH, you're hurting every member of the cast. Plus, you need to explain why they should remove her, the only legal president out there is JD's loss in the UK lawsuit. You also need to understand that until there is something to go against that ruling, they aren't going to change a damned thing nor should they!

I find it hilarious that you think that what happens in the US is somehow going to have any impact on viewers outside of the US. Don't forget that JD LOST his lawsuit and the appeal in the UK and that is all the international folks will ever see because they do not watch out news. Once again, your boycott isn't going to affect AH in any way, the only thing it does is hurt the innocent people that are in the movie with her. I mean, do you really think it is right to ruin this for the other actors just because you dislike Johnny Depp's ex-wife? You do understand that the man doesn't know you, he has no idea that you exist, and he couldn't give a damn what people say on the internet. In fact, based on what we know of him he would be very upset about you trying to sabotage the movie and ruin the other innocent actors that are in it just because his ex-wife is also in it. comment: It's very easy to hurt these big budget movies. Do note two things when figuring out how much a movie needs to break even. First, domestic theater owners get a %45-%50 cut of the gross box office (an even higher % for foreign box office %65-%75 cut, yes the studio only get%25-%35 of the foreign box office). Second the studio has to pay for marketing, which can equal the production budget up to around 150 million cap. These big budget movies operate on slim profit margins and it's easy to cut into this.
